Use the standard library
This is how to parse_nested_parens of paren_string:
  Remember that result is []
  Remember that depth is 0
  Remember that max_depth is 0

  Do this paren_string's length times:
    Remember that ch is item depth in paren_string

    When ch is "(", then:
      Increase depth
      When depth is more than max_depth, then:
        Remember that max_depth is depth
      End when
    End when

    When ch is ")", then:
      Decrease depth
    End when

    When ch is " ", then:
      When max_depth is more than 0, then:
        Add result to max_depth
        Remember that max_depth is 0
      End when
    End when
  End do

  When max_depth is more than 0, then:
    Add result to max_depth
  End when

  The answer is result
Now you know